id) into position then steam <b>12 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Meanwhile, crumple 2-4 sheets baking paper (depending on number of fish fillets), twist together at the ends and shape into boats. Remove Varoma, then add steamed peppers from Varoma to bowl with couscous and mix. Distribute couscous mixture in Varoma dish and leave a hole in the centre for steam to circulate."},{"content":"Dab some marinade off the fish fillets with paper towels. Place fillets in prepared paper boats, seal them and place on Varoma tray. Insert Varoma tray into Varoma dish, place covered Varoma into position and steam <b>7 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Set covered Varoma aside. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and set aside. Transfer fish stock from mixing bowl to a jug."},{"content":"Place 150 g fish stock from jug, red peppers from simmering basket, ¼ tsp salt and sugar to mixing bowl then purée <b>30 sec\/speed 7<b>."},{"content":"Arrange couscous mixture and fish fillets on serving plates, pour over a little pepper sauce and serve sprinkled with chopped coriander."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Red mullet has thick bones, which can be easily removed with tweezers before cooking.","Ras el hanout is a spice blend of coriander seeds, cinnamon, cloves, ginger, cardamom and a few other spices. A recipe for this can be found in the collection <i>Moroccan Adventure<\/i>.","Harissa is a spicy paste made from chilli, cumin, coriander seeds, garlic, salt and oil. A recipe for this can also be found in the collection <i>Moroccan Adventure<\/i>.","Lemon-salt paste is a great way to preserve lemons and can be used anywhere lemon peel or juice and a pinch of salt is required."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","40m","4 portions"]}